<h2>Add a status update</h2>

<p>Status updates allow you to provide narrative updates on project progress, keeping stakeholders informed about what's happening with your project.</p>

<h3>When to add a status update</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Regular progress updates (weekly, monthly, or as needed)</li>
    <li>Significant milestones or achievements</li>
    <li>Changes in project direction or scope</li>
    <li>Important decisions or outcomes</li>
    <li>Challenges or blockers that need visibility</li>
</ul>

<h3>How to add a status update</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Navigate to your project's detail page</li>
    <li>Click on the <strong>Overview</strong> tab (or any tab where status updates are visible)</li>
    <li>In the <strong>Status updates</strong> section, click <strong>Add status update</strong></li>
    <li>Enter your narrative update in the text area</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Save</strong> to publish your update</li>
</ul>

<h3>Best practices</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Be clear and concise - focus on key information</li>
    <li>Include context for stakeholders who may not be familiar with the project</li>
    <li>Update regularly to maintain visibility</li>
    <li>Use status updates to complement RAG status changes</li>
    <li>Link to relevant milestones, deliverables, or other project items when relevant</li>
</ul>

<h3>Editing status updates</h3>
<p>You can edit your status updates after creation by clicking on the update in the list and selecting <strong>Edit</strong>. This is useful for correcting errors or adding additional information.</p>

